29/09/2003
SARAJEVO, Bosnia and Herzegovina (BiH) -- A survey by the UNDP finds that 24 per cent of young people in BiH want to leave the country in search of more opportunity. The poll, released Saturday (27 September), surveyed 1,000 people between the ages of 15 and 30. In all, 40 per cent said they would like to leave for economic reasons, while 13 per cent want to continue their education abroad. (BHTV 1, AFP - 27/09/03)
